        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 4:17PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 417 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Calhoun, moving east at
10 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Calhoun, Resaca, Plainville, Sonoraville, Oostanaula, Sugar Valley,
Redbud, Nickelsville, and Audubon.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
